@page "/about"

<PageTitle>Smartie · About</PageTitle>

<div class="about-page">
    <header class="about-header">
        <p class="edition-badge">Community Edition</p>
        <h1>Smartie</h1>
        <p class="about-tagline">Your AI-powered productivity operating system — local-first, private, and bring-your-own-AI.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h2>What this edition includes</h2>
        <ul class="about-list">
            <li>No login, no subscription, no billing</li>
            <li>All conversations and settings stored in local SQLite</li>
            <li>You provide your own API keys (encrypted on this device)</li>
            <li>Choose Gemini, OpenAI, OpenRouter, or Ollama in Settings</li>
            <li>Desktop-first experience (MAUI) with an optional web UI for development</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Your data stays local</h2>
        <p>Smartie Community Edition runs entirely on your machine. Chat history, provider settings, and encrypted API keys never leave your device except when calling the AI provider you configured.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section about-future">
        <h2>Smartie Cloud</h2>
        <p class="about-cloud-note">
            <span class="badge badge-soon">Coming soon</span>
            A future hosted edition with sign-in, cloud sync, and managed AI access. Not available in Community Edition and not required to use Smartie today.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
